Trash80 bitmap font

The software contains a bitmap font rendered from Trash80's original work:
https://fontstruct.com/fontstructions/show/413734/stealth57

The font embedded in the source tree is originally licensed under CC-BY-SA 3.0:
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/

-----------

SDL_inprint bitmap font routine

The software contains portions of public domain code from driedfruit's
SDL_inprint bitmap font routine:
https://github.com/driedfruit/SDL_inprint

Relevant files include SDL2_inprint.h and inprint2.c. The retained filename
SDL2_inprint.h reflects the source file's provenance; the current project links
against SDL3, not SDL2.

-----------

libserialport example code

The software may contain serial-port example code derived from libserialport
examples, including code used by the M8 serial backend.

Source: https://sigrok.org/wiki/Libserialport
Licence: LGPL-3.0-or-later

-----------

rxi/ini

The software contains the Tiny ANSI C INI parser by rxi.

Source: https://github.com/rxi/ini
Licence: MIT
Copyright (c) 2016 rxi


-----------

External dependencies

This project depends on third-party software that is installed separately or
built during setup. These dependencies remain under their own licences.

-----------

SDL3

Used for display, input, and platform integration.

Source: https://github.com/libsdl-org/SDL
Licence: zlib

-----------

SDL3_ttf

Used for TrueType font rendering.

Source: https://github.com/libsdl-org/SDL_ttf
Licence: zlib

SDL3_ttf may use additional third-party libraries, such as FreeType, HarfBuzz,
PlutoSVG, and PlutoVG, under their respective licences depending on how it is
built and distributed.

-----------

libusb

Used for USB device access.

Source: https://github.com/libusb/libusb
Licence: LGPL-2.1-or-later

-----------

Mido

Used by the Python scripts for MIDI message creation, stream handling, virtual
ports, and message parsing.

Source: https://github.com/mido/mido
Licence: MIT
Copyright (c) 2013 Ole Martin Bjorndalen
Copyright (c) 2023 Raphael Doursenaud

-----------

python-rtmidi

Used as the backend module for real-time MIDI input/output from Python.

Source: https://github.com/SpotlightKid/python-rtmidi
Licence: MIT
Copyright (c) 2012-2023 Christopher Arndt

python-rtmidi includes or wraps RtMidi:

RtMidi: realtime MIDI input/output C++ classes
Source: https://github.com/thestk/rtmidi
Licence: Modified MIT
Copyright (c) 2003-2019 Gary P. Scavone